<span id="freeTextContainer9972915658508278851">I have completed the entire Sacks&apos;s oeuvre, with the single exception of <a href='https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/66723.Seeing_Voices' title='Seeing Voices by Oliver Sacks' rel='nofollow noopener'>Seeing Voices</a>. Oliver Sacks has been one of those life altering writers for me. He has changed the way I see the world. The great revelation with this volume for me was just how commonplace hallucinations are. There are myriad reasons why the brain might produce them: sensory deprivation, disease, drugs, etc.—many of them surprisingly benign. Fascinating and highly recommended. <br/><br/>Also see Will Self&apos;s review at: <a target='_blank' rel='noopener nofollow' href='http://www.guardian.co.uk/books/2012/nov/08/hallucinations-oliver-sacks-review'>http://www.gua</a></span>
